<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-0F-8koWWag491Eb2DAE0YQ" name=",_sFPC4DAWEeOzAouxgBZboA" guid="-0F-8koWWag491Eb2DAE0YQ" authors="http://www.webcredible.co.uk/user-friendly-resources/web-usability/user-centered-design.shtml" changeDate="2013-10-08T14:52:48.501+0200">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p&#xD;
style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; TEXT-TRANSFORM: none; BACKGROUND-COLOR: rgb(35,122,169); MARGIN-TOP: 1.1em; TEXT-INDENT: 0px; LETTER-SPACING: normal; FONT: 14px/20px arial, 'trebuchet MS', helvetica, sans-serif; WHITE-SPACE: normal; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 1.1em; COLOR: rgb(255,255,255); WORD-SPACING: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;a style=&quot;COLOR: rgb(255,167,65); CURSOR: pointer; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; TEXT-DECORATION: none&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;http://www.webcredible.co.uk/services/usability-testing.shtml&quot;>&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;>Usability testing&lt;/font>&lt;/a>&lt;span&#xD;
    class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span>sessions evaluate a site by collecting data from people as they use it. A&#xD;
    person is invited to attend a session in which they'll be asked to perform a series of tasks while a moderator takes&#xD;
    note of any difficulties they encounter.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p&#xD;
style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; TEXT-TRANSFORM: none; BACKGROUND-COLOR: rgb(35,122,169); MARGIN-TOP: 1.1em; TEXT-INDENT: 0px; LETTER-SPACING: normal; FONT: 14px/20px arial, 'trebuchet MS', helvetica, sans-serif; WHITE-SPACE: normal; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 1.1em; COLOR: rgb(255,255,255); WORD-SPACING: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px&quot;>&#xD;
    Users can be asked to follow the think-aloud protocol which asks them to&lt;span&#xD;
    class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span>&lt;strong>verbalise what they're doing and why they're doing it&lt;/strong>.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p&#xD;
style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; TEXT-TRANSFORM: none; BACKGROUND-COLOR: rgb(35,122,169); MARGIN-TOP: 1.1em; TEXT-INDENT: 0px; LETTER-SPACING: normal; FONT: 14px/20px arial, 'trebuchet MS', helvetica, sans-serif; WHITE-SPACE: normal; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 1.1em; COLOR: rgb(255,255,255); WORD-SPACING: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px&quot;>&#xD;
    You can also time users to see how long it takes them to complete tasks, which is a good measure of efficiency&#xD;
    (although you should bear in mind that using the 'think aloud' protocol will slow users down considerably).&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p&#xD;
style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: left; TEXT-TRANSFORM: none; BACKGROUND-COLOR: rgb(35,122,169); MARGIN-TOP: 1.1em; TEXT-INDENT: 0px; LETTER-SPACING: normal; FONT: 14px/20px arial, 'trebuchet MS', helvetica, sans-serif; WHITE-SPACE: normal; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 1.1em; COLOR: rgb(255,255,255); WORD-SPACING: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Two specialists&lt;/strong>' time is normally required per session - one to moderate, one to note problems.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
